com.MAVLink.common

Class msg_param_map_rc

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.MAVLink.Messages.MAVLinkMessage
      • com.MAVLink.common.msg_param_map_rc
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class msg_param_map_rc
extends MAVLinkMessage
    Bind a RC channel to a parameter. The parameter should change accoding to the RC channel value.
    See Also:

      • param_value_max

      • param_index

        public short param_index
        Parameter index. Send -1 to use the param ID field as identifier (else the param id will be ignored), send -2 to disable any existing map for this rc_channel_index.

      • param_id

        public byte[] param_id
        Onboard parameter id, terminated by NULL if the length is less than 16 human-readable chars and WITHOUT null termination (NULL) byte if the length is exactly 16 chars - applications have to provide 16+1 bytes storage if the ID is stored as string

      • parameter_rc_channel_index

        public short parameter_rc_channel_index
        Index of parameter RC channel. Not equal to the RC channel id. Typically correpsonds to a potentiometer-knob on the RC.
